<br>
Serious maxing up melee skills is not that important, it's nice to have them up, I'm personnally maxed in most of them (off/def/1hb/2hb/piercing/trowing (should get to working hand to hand i guess)) and while not really something that makes or break a mage, it's nice when you get jumped by that annoying aggro level 35 mob and you can just sheild yourself and melee it to death. It's also fun to get a melee kill on yelinak (yes happened to me) cuz then you can rub it in the face of the gadzillion monks rangers rogues and various other melee that YOU, the puny little mage, got the melee kill shot. It's also fun to land a 167 hit (my max!) on a mob and have people go uh? Mages can crush for 167? So really above level 20 or so (it's somewhat useful pre 20 to have decent melee skills), only defense really matters to max out, so get hit a lot! The others max out too low to be of any real use.<br>
<br>
Here's the cap at 60s (note that there's pre 50 cap too)<br>
<br>
offense/defense : 145<br>
weapon skills (1hb, 2hb, piercing): 110<br>
trowing: 75<br>
<br>
The max I ever reach with one of the best combo a melee mage can get (staff of silent star/primal 2hb/tola's robe) is about 20 DPS and that's counting proc damage, full buffs and avatar on me.<br>
<br>
While this may seem nice, my DPS using no mana (BoBC) is 35+, so it's really more of a fun factor still. =)<br>
<br>
Max out defense, do your best for rest but don't sweat it unless you want to beat lvl 51 rangers in melee at 60 (don't remember his name, but still feel sorry for him). bwuhahahaha <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</A>&nbsp<A href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&ltTDE&gt</A><BR>
